{"type":"message","id":"0e68faa6","parentId":"743200e1","timestamp":"2026-04-14T10:13:10.352Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me compare:\n\n**Last state (10:00 UTC):**\nActive: cron:ed2d0b5d, cron:6f3323ef, cron:e7885813, telegram:group:-5163901258\nBlocker: Telegram gateway timeout to group -5163901258\n\n**Current (10:09 UTC):**\nActive: cron:6f3323ef (me), cron:ed2d0b5d, cron:e7885813, telegram:group:-5163901258, cron:ac986a8d\n+ telegram:direct:6053576134 is now FAILED (was already failed at 10:00? or just ended?)\n\n\nThe Lead's direct Telegram session ran from 10:18 to 10:25 UTC, completing its API testing task at 10:08:14. Meanwhile, the monitoring cron that was supposed to send messages to the Telegram group appears to have been interrupted, though the cron itself is still active. This represents a shift from the 10:00 UTC snapshot where only the four core cron jobs were running.\n\nComparing the two states, the critical change is that the Lead's session successfully finished—unlike the failed sub-agents that hit the `providerSpecificData` error, this one completed cleanly. The main blocker I'm tracking is the Telegram gateway timeout preventing delivery to the group, which was already flagged as an issue at 10:00 and persists through 10:05. The cron:ac986a8d session started but may have stalled during delivery attempts. I should flag this as a new reportable event.","thinkingSignature":"3b3d86fb16cc96e30599d50c07d601df5318c6e18d195cf8d7961304dcdb1f41"},{"type":"text","text":"Changes detected. Updating state and sending report.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_25hf4tzneqkl_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/memory/heartbeat-state.json","content":"{\n  \"lastReport\": \"10:09 UTC 14 Apr\",\n  \"lastReportTimestamp\": 1776161340,\n  \"currentTimestamp\": 1776161340,\n  \"activeSessions\": [\n    \"cron:ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a